RACE.FOOTNOTES: INEXORABLE tracked along the inside, gained ground in the three to four path around the turn, took aim on the new leader while floated to the six path entering the lane, took contact from that one in upper stretch, bid while receiving another bump at the furlong grounds, then drove clear leaving the sixteenth pole. MUCHO MOJO stalked in the four to three path into the turn, bid and assumed command passing the five sixteenths pole, drifted to the five path as an outer rival took aim entering the lane, leaned into and bumped that one in upper stretch, did so again while battling into the final furlong but was bested with a sixteenth to go. MASTER GAME laid off of the pace in the five to six path, shifted inwardly in upper stretch and ran on to gain show late. TRIGGER HAPPY brushed with an outer rival at the start, set the pace along the inside, built a clear margin down the backstretch, but proved no match for an outer bidder at the five sixteenths pole, kept on but lost show late. JEDREK lagged behind, cut the gap in upper stretch, altered out in midstretch and moved up. SANT' ANTIMO tracked two wide, urged along in the four path around the turn and tired between horses. SKATE TO HEAVEN brushed with an inner rival at the start, chased in the two path and weakened.
